⊢ emit-program
  given redesign→§program' ≡ §«...the fully redesigned program...»
  given domain→description ≡ "An automated code review system that checks for security vulnerabilities, suggests fixes, and verifies the fixes don't break existing tests."
  yield final-cell-file

  ∴ Format the redesigned program as a complete .cell file...

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield final-cell-file ≡ "-- security-review.cell
-- An automated code review system that checks for security vulnerabilities,
-- suggests fixes, and verifies the fixes don't break existing tests.
--
-- Architecture: parse diff → classify risk regions → spawn per-region scanners →
-- collect findings → suggest fixes (if any) → run tests → compile report.
-- Zero-vulnerability path handled via given? and guard-induced ⊥.

⊨? on failure:
  retry with «oracle.failures» appended to prompt
  max 3 attempts
⊨? on exhaustion:
  error-value(⊥)

⊢ diff-input
  given raw-diff
  given test-manifest
  yield raw-diff, test-manifest
  ⊨ raw-diff is a valid unified diff format
  ⊨ test-manifest lists test names and expected outcomes

⊢ parse-diff ▸ crystallized
  given diff-input→raw-diff
  yield file-list[], change-regions[]
  ⊢= parse unified diff into structured file list and change regions
  ⊨ length(file-list) ≥ 1
  ⊨ each change-region maps to a file in file-list

⊢ classify-changes
  given parse-diff→change-regions
  yield risk-regions[]
  ∴ Classify each change region by risk level:
    high (auth, crypto, input handling), medium (data flow, API),
    low (UI, logging, comments).
  ⊨ each region has a risk level ∈ { \"high\", \"medium\", \"low\" }
  ⊨ risk-regions covers all change-regions

⊢⊢ spawn-scanners
  given classify-changes→risk-regions where any(risk-regions, r -> r→risk != \"low\")
  given §vuln-scan-template
  yield §scan-cells[]
  until length(scan-cells) = count(risk-regions, r -> r→risk != \"low\")
  max 20
  accumulate

⊢ vuln-scan-template
  given region
  given risk-level
  yield findings[], severity
  ∴ Scan «region» for vulnerability patterns appropriate to «risk-level».
  ⊨ each finding has type, location, severity, and evidence
  ⊨ severity ∈ { \"critical\", \"high\", \"medium\", \"low\", \"info\" }

⊢ collect-findings
  given vuln-scan-*→findings
  given vuln-scan-*→severity
  yield all-findings[], has-vulnerabilities
  ⊢= all-findings ← flatten(vuln-scan-*→findings)
  ⊢= has-vulnerabilities ← len(all-findings) > 0

⊢ suggest-fixes
  given collect-findings→all-findings where collect-findings→has-vulnerabilities = true
  given parse-diff→file-list
  yield patches[], explanations[]
  ∴ For each vulnerability, generate a concrete code fix with explanation.
  ⊨ length(patches) = length(collect-findings→all-findings)
  ⊨ each patch is syntactically valid code
  ⊨ each explanation describes the vulnerability and the fix

⊢ run-tests
  given? suggest-fixes→patches
  given diff-input→test-manifest
  given parse-diff→file-list
  yield test-results[], all-pass
  ∴ If «suggest-fixes→patches» is ⊥, run tests against original code.
    Otherwise, apply patches and run tests. Report pass/fail per test.
  ⊨ test-results covers every test in test-manifest
  ⊢= all-pass ← all(test-results, t -> t→status = \"pass\")

⊢ compile-report
  given collect-findings→all-findings
  given collect-findings→has-vulnerabilities
  given? suggest-fixes→patches
  given? suggest-fixes→explanations
  given run-tests→test-results
  given run-tests→all-pass
  yield review-report
  ∴ Compile final security review report. If no vulnerabilities, report clean.
    Otherwise: summary by severity, findings with fixes, test impact, verdict.
  ⊨ contains(review-report, \"Summary\") and contains(review-report, \"Findings\") and contains(review-report, \"Verdict\")
  ⊨ if has-vulnerabilities = false then contains(review-report, \"clean\")
  ⊨ if all-pass = true and has-vulnerabilities = true then contains(review-report, \"safe to merge\")
  ⊨ if all-pass = false then contains(review-report, \"regressions\")"

