⊢= obs-guard-clause-convergence
  given §05-meta-cell-designer
  yield observations ≡ "GUARD CLAUSE AS CONVERGENCE SIGNAL: The v0.2 guard clause on critique (len(awkward-spots) > 0) creates a clean convergence mechanism for the ⊢∘ loop. In iteration 1, the guard passes (4 awkward spots) and critique produces problems. In iteration 2, the guard fails (0 awkward spots) and critique is SKIPPED, yielding ⊥ for problems. The ⊢∘ until condition 'len(problems) = 0 or problems = ⊥' catches this ⊥ as convergence. This is more elegant than the R16 version which used 'length(critique→problems) = 0' alone — the guard clause prevents critique from even executing when there's nothing to critique, saving an LLM call. The guard + ⊥ + given? chain is a v0.2-native convergence pattern."

⊢= obs-given-question-mark-resilience
  given §05-meta-cell-designer
  yield observations ≡ "GIVEN? ENABLES GRACEFUL DEGRADATION: redesign uses given? for critique→problems and critique→suggestions. In iteration 2, when critique is skipped (guard false), these resolve to ⊥. The ∴ body checks for ⊥ and passes the program through unchanged. This is the v0.2 'optional dependency' pattern working exactly as designed — the cell adapts its behavior based on whether upstream data is available. In the generated §program, the same pattern appears: run-tests uses given? suggest-fixes→patches to handle the zero-vulnerability case. The pattern composes: meta-program and designed program both use given? for the same reason (graceful handling of conditional paths)."

⊢= obs-aspirational-oracles
  given §05-meta-cell-designer
  yield observations ≡ "ASPIRATIONAL ORACLES UNDER ⊢∘: design-cells has 5 oracles that describe ideal output quality (valid syntax, complete coverage, dataflow correctness, uses ⊢=, uses ⊨). Under ⊢∘ management, these are aspirational — they provide feedback but don't independently block freezing. In iteration 1, all 5 aspirational oracles pass on the first attempt. This means the distinction between aspirational and hard oracles is invisible in THIS execution. The distinction would matter if design-cells produced a program missing ⊢= cells (aspirational oracle fails but ⊢∘ still proceeds to critique/redesign, where the issue would be caught). The safety net is there even though it wasn't needed."

⊢= obs-meta-program-design-quality
  given §05-meta-cell-designer
  yield observations ≡ "DESIGN EVOLUTION ARC: The generated §program went through a genuine improvement cycle. Iteration 1 produced a working but flawed design (4 problems: broken zero-vuln path, undefined test suite, vague oracle, blocked compile-report). Iteration 2's redesign fixed all 4 with v0.2 features: given? for optional paths, test-manifest as explicit input, contains() for structural oracles, conditional oracle for clean verdict. The critique identified a REAL bug (zero-vuln hang) that would be missed without systematic trace-readiness and oracle simulation. This validates the meta-cell-designer's architecture: decompose → design → trace → simulate → critique → redesign catches genuine design errors."

⊢= obs-quotation-depth
  given §05-meta-cell-designer
  yield observations ≡ "NESTED § QUOTATION: This program operates at two levels of quotation. The outer program (meta-cell-designer) yields §program which is a Cell program containing its own §vuln-scan-template. This is § inside §. The outer program reasons ABOUT the inner program's cells without executing them. The inner program's ⊢⊢ spawn-scanners would execute vuln-scan-template at runtime, but the meta-level only inspects it. This is the v0.2 open question #9 (nested quotation depth) in action. The meta-cell-designer works because it treats §program as opaque text — it never tries to evaluate the inner § references. Two levels of quotation is the practical maximum for LLM comprehension."

⊢= obs-zero-vuln-path-discovery
  given §05-meta-cell-designer
  yield observations ≡ "⊥ PROPAGATION BUG FOUND AND FIXED: The most significant finding is AWKWARD-2: the original design hangs on clean code (no vulnerabilities). This is a class of bug unique to Cell — guard-induced ⊥ creating unintended blockages in downstream cells. The fix (given? on run-tests and compile-report) is the canonical v0.2 pattern for handling optional data paths. This bug would be nearly invisible in traditional programming (you'd just have an if/else) but in Cell's dataflow model, a skipped cell produces ⊥ that propagates and blocks. The trace-readiness + simulate-oracles + critique pipeline caught this systematically. Cell programs need ⊥-propagation analysis as a standard quality gate."

⊢= obs-frame-count-efficiency
  given §05-meta-cell-designer
  yield observations ≡ "EXECUTION BUDGET: 12 eval-one steps (plus 1 guard skip) for a program that designs, traces, simulates, critiques, and redesigns another program. The ⊢∘ loop adds 5 extra frames (frames 8-12 for iteration 2). Without the evolution loop, the program would complete in 7 frames but produce a flawed design. The 5-frame overhead buys 4 concrete bug fixes. The evolution loop cost is proportional to the number of problems found, not the program size — a well-designed initial program could converge in 1 iteration (0 extra frames). The guard clause on critique means iteration 2 skips 1 LLM call (critique itself), so the actual LLM cost of iteration 2 is 4 calls, not 5."
